    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-10-16T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-10-16T10:00:00-05:00" n="742"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d742">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">838.51/997: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bailly-Blanchard</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Port au Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-10-16T10:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 16, 1920—10 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 10:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>78. Department’s 341, of September 9, 1920. Financial Adviser concurs in plan
                    outlined by Department but suggests $175,000 be set aside monthly instead of
                    $200,000 and applied as follows by Receiver General: Interest and amortization
                    foreign debt, $136,626.74, computed at par; interest on Banque Nationale debt,
                        $8,665.78;<note n="86" xml:id="d742fn86">Annual interest on Haitian
                        Government’s note for $1,733,154.87 held by the Banque Nationale was
                        $108,989.29.</note> interest <pb facs="0932" n="842" xml:id="pg_842"/>
                    guaranty National Railroad, $17,500;<note n="87" xml:id="d742fn87">Annual
                        interest guaranty, $248,120.71.</note> interest guaranty, $3,440, and
                    amortization [of arrears?] of interest guaranty, $2,880, P C S Railroad<note
                        n="88" xml:id="d742fn88">Compagnie des Chemins de Fer de la Plaine du
                        Cul-de-Sac; annual interest guaranty, $41,280, and amortization of arrears,
                        $34,560.</note> [garbled group]. Saving on foreign debt service due to
                    depreciation of franc to be devoted proportionately to retirement Banque
                    Nationale debt and interest guaranty arrears National Railroad. Does Department
                    approve and desire that plan be put in operation at once?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Blanchard</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
